SEO promotion checklist for {{ project_name }}
================================================

GitHub (Phase 1 — GUIDE-1)
[ ] Paste about.txt into repo Description
[ ] Add topics from topics.txt
[ ] Merge readme-seo-sections.md into README (or replace with readme-seo.md)
[ ] Cross-link related repos and YouTube in README
[ ] Add license, .gitignore, releases if missing

YouTube (Phase 1–2)
[ ] Update channel About from youtube/channel-about.txt
[ ] Create playlists from youtube/playlists.txt
{% for video in youtube.videos %}
[ ] Upload video: {{ video.id }}
    [ ] Title from youtube/{{ video.id }}/title-variants.txt
    [ ] Description from youtube/{{ video.id }}/description.txt
    [ ] Tags from youtube/{{ video.id }}/tags.txt
    [ ] End screens from youtube/{{ video.id }}/end-screen-cards.txt
{% endfor %}

Social & backlinks (Phase 3)
[ ] Publish dev.to post → social/devto-post.md
[ ] Publish Medium post → social/medium-post.md
[ ] Post X thread → social/x-post-thread.txt
[ ] Share on Reddit → social/reddit-post.txt (check sub rules)
[ ] LinkedIn → social/linkedin-post.txt
[ ] Discord communities → social/discord-announcement.txt

Monitoring (Phase 4)
[ ] Google Search Console / YouTube Analytics — track search terms
[ ] GitHub traffic insights — referral sources
[ ] Iterate every 2–4 weeks on top-performing keywords
